The All Progressives Congress has extended deadline for the sale of its Expression of Interest and Nomination forms for aspirants seeking elective positions in the 2023 general election from May 6 to May 10. The APC National Publicity Secretary, Felix Morka, said this in a statement on Wednesday in Abuja. “In a revised timetable issued by the APC National Organising Secretary, Mr Sulaiman Muhammad Argungu, the last day for submission of completed forms and accompanying documents is now set for Wednesday, May 11,” he said. Morka said that the APC Congresses for election of local government, state and national delegates would hold from Thursday, May 12 to Saturday, May 14. The News Agency of Nigeria reports that the sale of Expression of Interest and Nomination to aspirants began on April 23. NAN